Sundance Resources Has 16% Stake Sold for A$191 Million

-- B y   J a s o n   S c o t t
-- 
2011-03-18T07:56:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/sundance-resources-has-16-stake-sold-for-a-191-million-1-.html
Sundance Resources Ltd., seeking to
develop a $3.4 billion  iron ore  mine in West Africa, today had
16 percent of its equity change hands in one transaction,
according to Bloomberg data.  Stock valued at about A$191 million ($190 million) was sold
on the Australian stock exchange. The 433.79 million shares were
sold at 44 cents each, with RBC Securities Australia Pty
handling the deal, according to the data.  Shares in the Perth-based company rose 4.3 percent to close
at 49 Australian cents in Sydney trading today. Paul Armstrong,
a spokesman for the company, declined to comment.  Sundance board members, including millionaire  Ken Talbot ,
were killed in a plane crash in the Republic of Congo in June.
Talbot held 433.79 million shares in Sundance, the same number
involved in today’s trade, according to the data.  Talbot, 59, was a director of Sundance and its largest
shareholder. He was  Australia ’s 33rd richest person with a
fortune of A$965 million, according to Business Review Weekly’s
annual Rich 200 list, published in May. Talbot Group has
investments in iron ore, uranium, liquefied natural gas, copper,
zinc, lead, molybdenum and nickel.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Jason Scott  in Perth at 
